HEADWORD: Chamade
<hw>Cha*made</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>chamade</ets>, fr. Pg. <ets>chamada</ets>, fr. <ets>chamar</ets> to
call, fr. L. <ets>clamare</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A signal
made for a parley by beat of a drum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They beat the <qex>chamade</qex>, and sent us carte blanche.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chamaecytisus</ent>⟦br⟧
